is\u001b[K\r\n| variable so that it is blank.\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n*/\u001b[K\r\n$\u001b[94mconfig\u001b[m\u000f[\u001b[92m'index_page'\u001b[m\u000f] = \u001b[92m'index.php'\u001b[m\u000f;\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n/*\u001b[K\r\n|--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[K\r\n| URI PROTOCOL\u001b[K\r\n|--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n| This item determines which server global should be used to retrieve the\u001b[K\r\n| URI string.  The default setting of 'REQUEST_URI' works for most servers.\u001b[K\r\n| If your links do not seem to work, try one of the other delicious flavors:\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n| 'REQUEST_URI'    Uses $_SERVER['REQUEST_URI']\u001b[K\r\n| 'QUERY_STRING'   Uses $_SERVER['QUERY_STRING']\u001b[K\r\n| 'PATH_INFO'      Uses $_SERVER['PATH_INFO']\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n| WARNING: If you set this to 'PATH_INFO', URIs will always be URL-decoded!\u001b[K\r\n*/\u001b[K\r\n$\u001b[94mconfig\u001b[m\u000f[\u001b[92m'uri_protocol'\u001b[m\u000f] = \u001b[92m'REQUEST_URI'\u001b[m\u000f;\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n/*\u001b[K\r\n|--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[K\r\n| URL suffix\u001b[K\r\n|--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n| This option allows you to add a suffix to all URLs generated by CodeIgniter.\u001b[K\r\n| For more information please see the user guide:\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n| https://codeigniter.com/user_guide/general/urls.html\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[0;10;7m\u000fapplication/config/config.php                                                                                                                                                                                                 1,1            Top\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[J\u001b[?112c\u001b[?112c\u001b[H<?php\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[96mdefined\u001b[m\u000f(\u001b[92m'BASEPATH'\u001b[m\u000f) OR \